CONFIG FILE LOCATED AT
THIS FILE CONTAIN USER SETTINGS

/etc/ssh/ssh_config

Now THIS FILE HAS TO COMPETE TO HIERCHY FOR AUTORITY LEVEL

[1] ssh_config		# comes at lowest level
[2] ~/.ssh/config	# comes at second level
[3] cli commands 	# comes at first level

use $ man ssh for more information

NOW LOOKING INTO CONFIG FILE

$ sudo vim /etc/ssh/ssh_config

WE CAN MANIPULATE MULTIPLE SETTINGS SUCH AS DEFAULT PORT WHER SSH AGENT WILL TRY TO LOGIN

TO MAKE YOUR OWN CONFIG FILE 
$ touch ~/.ssh/config

